[[[break]]]changed line 5 from: *orange {code Maybe the best idea is NOT to decide the case studies at this point, but instead to write the grant proposal based on theoretical concerns, explaining the need for case studies linked to those concerns, and spend the money partly on finding out which case studies illustrate the points.  That's better than jumping head-first into the wrong case studies and ending up spending lots of time on inconsequential empirical stuff.
